    "On the one hand, the Random Method is more suitable for small vector spaces, while the Distributed one generally requires large vector spaces.",
    "On the other hand, the Distributed Method fosters a better distribution of items, an aspect that may be critical in the Random Method, especially when dealing with a limited number of items.",
    "This method enables a more accurate representation of the impact of similarity on false memory, ensuring that even subtle variations, which might be missed with uncontrolled item distribution, are effectively captured.",
    "Thus, when selecting the method, these technical, methodological, and theoretical considerations should be taken into account.",
    "FMG offers maximum flexibility in allowing researchers to select and define the most suitable vector space to answer theoretical questions."
